dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha run out (Rahane) 72 (100b 9x4 0x6 128m) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: oh looks like he's run out with a direct hit! Sikandar went deep in the crease to turn the ball to midwicket and said no only after taking a couple of steps. Chamu had come way out of the crease by now, nearly haflway down, and his dive also could not save him because of Rahane's direct hit. Jinxy the cat

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c Patel b Binny 32 (41b 3x4 0x6 57m) SR: 78.04

dismissalComment.html: can't make it three in a row, but holes out! He did connect much better this time, slammed the full delivery down the ground but only found Axar at long off for an easy catch
not this time, gets the edge and he's caught behind! Lovely seam position of the ball, facing the slip, shapes away from the batsman as he opens the face of the bat for a single catch to the keeper

stunning catch from Jinxy cat! Elton stayed back for the short of length ball as it shaped away, poked and get a thick edge towards second slip actually and Jinxy leapt like a cat to his right to grab that with both hands. Umpires checking for no ball, and if the catch is clean. Not a no ball, and the umpires checking if the ball touched the ground when Rahane landed after his inter-galatic leap. The ball was mainly in his right hand when the elbows hit the ground and looks like some fingers were under the ball. Elton has to go back

that's one more wicket, and another good fielding effort by Rahane! Graeme pulled the back of length ball and mistimed it, making the ball lob towards extra cover and Rahane took a few steps before diving forward to his left for a sliding catch with both hands. Jinxy the cat

dismissalComment.html: that's it, taken at mid-off, and India finish it off. It was pitched up slightly, Donald chipped it down in the air and Axar had to dive forward to get his hands under it. Good catch seals the series win

dismissalText.commentary: Donald Tiripano c Patel b Kumar 6 (13b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 46.15

commentTextItems.html: that's it, taken at mid-off, and India finish it off. It was pitched up slightly, Donald chipped it down in the air and Axar had to dive forward to get his hands under it. Good catch seals the series win

commentPostTextItems.html: Chigumbura: Losing three wickets in first 11 overs made us lose today, something we need to work on from next game. Was a much better wicket today and a chaseable score, we thought they'd score 300 but we managed to pull it back. Unfortunately didn't back it with the bat.

Rahane: We were looking for 280-290 but we batted pretty well and partnership between me and Vijay was crucial and later with Rayudu. Wicket was slow early but got even slower in second innings and we have a good experienced attack with quality spinners. It wasn't easy for batting but we bowled well. Our bowlers were upto the mark, they bowled in right areas and fielding was right up there.

Man of the Match Vijay: It was a great opportunity for me to prove myself, I wasn't getting my flow right but still helped in the opening partnership. The wicket was much better today, a bit on the slower side but we adjusted to it.

That's all from the second ODI, and from the series for today. Hope you enjoyed it as much as we did, bringing the coverage to you. Keep an eye on Bangladesh's chase or the Wimbledon final if you don't know what else to do on a Sunday. Until the next match, goodbye and good luck!

4.49pm A much better all-round performance from India today, so much stronger with the bat, excellent on the field, and better bowling to lead 2-0. Zimbabwe didn't bowl badly after opting to field, but the Indian batsmen were tough to dismiss today. Zimbabwe dropped a couple of catches too and were eventually beaten by 62 runs, India take the series.
Federer takes the second set, what a thrilling tie-breaker!

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha run out (Rahane) 72 (100b 9x4 0x6 128m) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: oh looks like he's run out with a direct hit! Sikandar went deep in the crease to turn the ball to midwicket and said no only after taking a couple of steps. Chamu had come way out of the crease by now, nearly haflway down, and his dive also could not save him because of Rahane's direct hit. Jinxy the cat

headshotImage.caption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Uthappa b Kumar 5 (11b 1x4 0x6 15m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: not this time, gets the edge and he's caught behind! Lovely seam position of the ball, facing the slip, shapes away from the batsman as he opens the face of the bat for a single catch to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Rahane b Kumar 9 (6b 2x4 0x6 10m) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: stunning catch from Jinxy cat! Elton stayed back for the short of length ball as it shaped away, poked and get a thick edge towards second slip actually and Jinxy leapt like a cat to his right to grab that with both hands. Umpires checking for no ball, and if the catch is clean. Not a no ball, and the umpires checking if the ball touched the ground when Rahane landed after his inter-galatic leap. The ball was mainly in his right hand when the elbows hit the ground and looks like some fingers were under the ball. Elton has to go back

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams b Patel 20 (37b 1x4 0x6 57m) SR: 54.05

dismissalComment.html: it's gone through to knock over the off stump! Axar got this one to turn in as Sean came forward to work it to leg with the spin, but he played the wrong line as the ball pitched just outside off and turned in sharply to go through the gate

dismissalComment.html: he's edged, he's dropped, no he's taken in fact, umpire says no but he walks! Sikandar cut off the back foot as the ball came in, got an edge and the ball lobbed off the keeper's pads square of the wicket and Robbie dived to his right to catch that. Umpire didn't move but Sikandar walked back

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalComment.html: can't make it three in a row, but holes out! He did connect much better this time, slammed the full delivery down the ground but only found Axar at long off for an easy catch

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer c Rahane b Kumar 27 (42b 2x4 0x6 65m) SR: 64.28

dismissalComment.html: that's one more wicket, and another good fielding effort by Rahane! Graeme pulled the back of length ball and mistimed it, making the ball lob towards extra cover and Rahane took a few steps before diving forward to his left for a sliding catch with both hands. Jinxy the cat

dismissalText.commentary: Neville Madziva run out (Rahane) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: looks like a run out! Graeme creamed the ball straight to cover, Rahane collected and threw it quickly to the bowler's end, that too with a direct hit. He's been superb in the field today, Jinxy the cat
